### Problem02
Look at the following two Java functions:

```java
public static double recursive_harmonic(int n )
    {
        if(n==1) return 1.0;
        return recursive_harmonic(n-1)+1.0/n;
    }

public static double not_recursive_harmonic(int n )
    {
        double value=0;
        for (int i =1;i<=n;i++)
        {
            value+=1.0/i;
        }
        return value;
    }
```
Please select choices that are correct.

**Choices:**

a. The 'recursive_harmonic()' takes exactly the same memory space as the 'not_recursive_harmonic()' method.

b. There are situations when iteration (loop) is the only option rather than recursion that is avalibable to address a problem. 

c. Any recursive function can be replaced by an iterative counterpart.

d. System keeps track of each recursive call in Java using a data structure called stack.

